data.title: Dame Henrietta Barnett and Canon Samuel Barnett
data.meta_description: Location: Spaniards Road, Hampstead, London, England Dame Henrietta Barnett 1851-1936 Founder of Hamsptead Garden Suburb and Canon Samuel Barnett 1844-1913 Social Reformer lived here Greater London Council "Hampstead Garden Suburb is a suburb, situated North of Hampstead, to the West of Highgate, and East of Golders Green. It is an example of early 20th Century domestic architecture and town planning located in the London Borough of Barnet in North West London. The master plan was prepared by Barry Parker and Sir Raymond Unwin." en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hampstead_Garden_Suburb "Dame Henrietta Octavia Weston Barnett (née Rowland), DBE (4 May 1851 – 10 June 1936) was a notable English social reformer and author. She and her husband, Samuel Augustus Barnett, founded the first 'University Settlement' at Toynbee Hall (in the East End of London) in 1884." en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henrietta_Barnett

Greater London Council

"Hampstead Garden Suburb is a suburb, situated North of Hampstead, to the West of Highgate, and East of Golders Green. It is an example of early 20th Century domestic architecture and town planning located in the London Borough of Barnet in North West London. The master plan was prepared by Barry Parker and Sir Raymond Unwin."

en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hampstead_Garden_Suburb

"Dame Henrietta Octavia Weston Barnett (née Rowland), DBE (4 May 1851 – 10 June 1936) was a notable English social reformer and author. She and her husband, Samuel Augustus Barnett, founded the first 'University Settlement' at Toynbee Hall (in the East End of London) in 1884."
